Actress Etinosa Idemudia has appealed to parents with male children to do better in grooming them for posterity sake. The “Blood of Enogie” star actress, squealed at the level of moral decadence among the human masculine gender of today. According to Idemudia, a mother of one, every parent with male children owe those with female kids a duty to ensure the proper upbringing of their sons.   My battle with sickle cell, by Adekunle Gold     Asake for maiden SPOB jive     Baba Ijesha: Yomi Fabiyi’s estranged lover cancels…   Concerned about her young daughter’s future, the single mother passionately begged parents to get it right with their sons insisting they actually need more training than daughters. The award winning actress wrote: “You people that have male children owe us o. You owe us that have female children. “Abeg train your boys because the kind radarada mentality I dey see for men of nowadays. Even men on Twitter. “I beg you well well. Make my pikin no jam agbako. “People like @nma_okocha, @ememinwang @francessben abeg abeg abegggggggg boys need marital training twice as much as ladies these days cos what!!!!! The things I’m hearing Omo!!! Omo × 1000,” she added.